tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, low total CO₂, and significant proteinuria, suggesting impaired renal function with possible metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals glucosuria, ketonuria, and proteinuria despite normal blood glucose and low HbA1c, which may indicate renal glycosuria or tubular dysfunction. Cloudy, brown urine with ammoniacal odor may suggest underlying urinary tract pathology. Prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended.
